    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s state sector to go full electric, no more fuel vehicles: president",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka will exclusively purchase electric vehicles for use in the state sector, President Ranil Wickremesinghe s aid.",
        "Presenting an interim budget for the remainder of the year, Wickremesinghe told parliament on Tuesday August 30 that the purchase of fuel-run vehicles for state services will be stopped.",
        "Sri Lanka is going through an energy crisis in the midst of the country\u2019s worst economic crisis since independence. Fuel queues, which had eased following the implementation of a digital quota system, have now returned, though the Power & Energy Ministry has assured the public that supply will continue as usual.",
        "Meanwhile, daily power cuts continue, though the duration of scheduled cuts have now reduced to two hours and 20 minutes. (Colombo/Aug30/2022)"
      ],
